---
import Deck from '../layouts/Deck.astro';
import AboutStakater from '../components/slides/AboutStakater.astro';
import Partnership from '../components/slides/Partnership.astro';
---
<Deck title="Stakater | Commercial Sales Executive" persona="Commercial Sales Executive">

  <!-- 1. Hero -->
  <section>
    <div class="container" style="text-align:center;">
      <h1>
        Turn One-Time Sales Into<br/>
        <span class="highlight">Expanding Accounts.</span>
      </h1>
      <br/><br/>
      <h2 style="color:#5a5668; font-weight:500; font-size:32px;">
        How Stakater drives portfolio pull-through and protects renewals.
      </h2>
    </div>

    <aside class="notes">
      <p class="notes-dir">Fast opening — commercial teams move quickly. Get to the value in 15 seconds.</p>
      <p class="notes-say">"What I want to show you is how to get more ARR from accounts you've already closed. Not new logos — your existing book. Specifically: more nodes, more products, stickier renewals. That's the conversation."</p>
    </aside>
  </section>

  <!-- 2. About Stakater -->
  <AboutStakater />

  <!-- 3. Partnership -->
  <Partnership />

  <!-- 4. The Commercial Problem -->
  <section>
    <div class="container" style="max-width:950px;">
      <h1>
        Mid-Market Accounts Don't Expand.<br/>
        <span class="highlight">They Churn.</span>
      </h1>
      <br/><br/>
      <div style="font-size:22px; line-height:1.8; color:#1A0D32; max-width:680px;">
        <p>
          Volume accounts close fast.<br/>
          Implementation completes.
        </p>
        <br/>
        <p>
          Platform sits underutilized.<br/>
          No one owns what happens next.
        </p>
        <br/>
        <p>
          Renewal arrives.<br/>
          Customer asks: "What did we get for this?"
        </p>
      </div>
      <br/><br/>
      <h2>
        Platform value must be <span class="highlight">demonstrated before renewal</span> — not after.
      </h2>
    </div>

    <aside class="notes">
      <p class="notes-dir">Read the room — most commercial AEs have felt this pain personally. Let the silence after "What did we get for this?" do work.</p>
      <p class="notes-say">"The commercial motion is built for velocity. Deals close fast. Implementation happens. And then the partner leaves. Six months later the platform is underutilized, nobody owns the customer relationship, and renewal arrives with a hard question — 'What did we actually get from this?' That's where churn lives. The answer to churn isn't a better renewal pitch. It's demonstrating value before the renewal conversation starts."</p>
    </aside>
  </section>

  <!-- 5. Pull-Through Opportunity -->
  <section class="section-light">
    <div class="container">
      <h1 style="text-align:center;">
        Every OpenShift Account Is a <span class="highlight">Portfolio Pipeline</span>
      </h1>
      <br/>
      <p style="text-align:center; margin:0 auto;">
        Customers need more than software. They need a working platform.
      </p>
      <br/><br/><br/>
      <div style="display:grid; grid-template-columns:1fr 1fr; gap:80px; align-items:start;">

        <div style="padding:30px; background:white; border-radius:12px;">
          <h3 style="color:#5a5668; margin-bottom:20px; font-size:20px; font-weight:600;">What Customers Buy</h3>
          <p style="font-size:18px; line-height:1.7; color:#1A0D32;">
            OpenShift subscription.<br/>
            Implementation project.<br/>
            Then silence.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div style="padding:30px; border-left:4px solid #FF5623;">
          <h3 style="margin-bottom:20px; font-size:20px; font-weight:600;">What Creates Pull-Through</h3>
          <p style="font-size:18px; line-height:1.7; color:#1A0D32;">
            Platform maturity → storage demand → ODF<br/>
            Multi-cluster growth → management → ACM<br/>
            Security requirements → runtime → ACS<br/>
            Event-driven architecture → streaming → AMQ
          </p>
        </div>

      </div>
      <br/><br/>
      <h2 style="text-align:center;">
        Stakater creates the platform conditions that make <span class="highlight">pull-through inevitable.</span>
      </h2>
    </div>

    <aside class="notes">
      <p class="notes-dir">Walk through the right column top to bottom. Each line is a pull-through deal moment.</p>
      <p class="notes-say">"Every OpenShift account has a natural portfolio expansion path. As the platform matures, storage needs emerge — that's ODF. As clusters multiply, management complexity forces a conversation — that's ACM. Security and compliance maturity creates the right moment for ACS. And as applications modernize, streaming architecture becomes inevitable — that's AMQ. These conversations don't happen by chance. They happen because a partner is there, managing the platform, and creating the conditions for the next product to land."</p>
    </aside>
  </section>

  <!-- 6. Portfolio Products We Drive -->
  <section>
    <div class="container">
      <h1 style="text-align:center;">
        Products We <span class="highlight">Pull Through</span>
      </h1>
      <br/><br/><br/>
      <div style="display:grid; grid-template-columns:repeat(4,1fr); gap:40px; text-align:center;">

        <div>
          <h2 style="color:#FF5623; font-size:32px; margin-bottom:14px;">ODF</h2>
          <p style="font-size:17px; color:#1A0D32;">Storage standardization for stateful workloads. Natural step as the platform matures.</p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h2 style="color:#FF5623; font-size:32px; margin-bottom:14px;">ACM</h2>
          <p style="font-size:17px; color:#1A0D32;">Multi-cluster management at scale. Inevitable once accounts have 2+ clusters.</p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h2 style="color:#FF5623; font-size:32px; margin-bottom:14px;">ACS</h2>
          <p style="font-size:17px; color:#1A0D32;">Kubernetes-native security. Triggered by compliance and governance maturity.</p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h2 style="color:#FF5623; font-size:32px; margin-bottom:14px;">AMQ</h2>
          <p style="font-size:17px; color:#1A0D32;">Event streaming. Unlocked as application workloads grow and modernize.</p>
        </div>

      </div>
      <br/><br/><br/>
      <h2 style="text-align:center;">
        We don't pitch products. We create the maturity that makes <span class="highlight">customers ask for them.</span>
      </h2>
    </div>

    <aside class="notes">
      <p class="notes-dir">Keep this fast — one line per product. The bottom line is the key message.</p>
      <p class="notes-say">"ODF, ACM, ACS, AMQ. These aren't upsell pitches — they're what mature OpenShift platforms naturally demand. We don't go in and pitch storage. We take the platform to a maturity level where the customer comes to us asking for storage. Same with multi-cluster management. Same with security. We create the conditions. The product conversations follow."</p>
    </aside>
  </section>

  <!-- 7. Commercial Outcomes -->
  <section class="section-light">
    <div class="container">
      <h1 style="text-align:center;">
        Accounts That <span class="highlight">Grew With Stakater</span>
      </h1>
      <br/><br/>
      <div style="display:grid; grid-template-columns:repeat(3,1fr); gap:28px;">

        <div style="background:white; padding:36px; border-radius:16px; box-shadow:0 12px 40px rgba(26,13,50,0.08); position:relative;">
          <div style="height:4px; background:#FF5623; position:absolute; top:0; left:0; right:0; border-radius:16px 16px 0 0;"></div>
          <div style="text-align:center; margin-bottom:20px; padding-top:8px;">
            <img src="/logos/csn.png" alt="CSN" style="height:50px;">
          </div>
          <p style="font-size:17px; color:#1A0D32; line-height:1.7;">
            Post-implementation gap closed.<br/><br/>
            <span class="highlight">Result:</span> Node growth + ODF adopted. Red Hat footprint expanded across storage and platform.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div style="background:white; padding:36px; border-radius:16px; box-shadow:0 12px 40px rgba(26,13,50,0.08); position:relative;">
          <div style="height:4px; background:#FF5623; position:absolute; top:0; left:0; right:0; border-radius:16px 16px 0 0;"></div>
          <div style="text-align:center; margin-bottom:20px; padding-top:8px;">
            <img src="/logos/atg.png" alt="ATG" style="height:50px;">
          </div>
          <p style="font-size:17px; color:#1A0D32; line-height:1.7;">
            Lifecycle ownership from Year 1.<br/><br/>
            <span class="highlight">Result:</span> 7 consecutive years of node growth. OpenShift became strategic.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div style="background:white; padding:36px; border-radius:16px; box-shadow:0 12px 40px rgba(26,13,50,0.08); position:relative;">
          <div style="height:4px; background:#FF5623; position:absolute; top:0; left:0; right:0; border-radius:16px 16px 0 0;"></div>
          <div style="text-align:center; margin-bottom:20px; padding-top:8px;">
            <img src="/logos/rs.png" alt="Region Skåne" style="height:50px;">
          </div>
          <p style="font-size:17px; color:#1A0D32; line-height:1.7;">
            Standardization-led expansion.<br/><br/>
            <span class="highlight">Result:</span> More nodes, additional clusters, new Red Hat products adopted.
          </p>
        </div>

      </div>
    </div>

    <aside class="notes">
      <p class="notes-dir">Land on the result line for each card. That's the commercial signal.</p>
      <p class="notes-say">"CSN — post-implementation gap, nodes flat, no portfolio adoption. We stepped in. Nodes grew, ODF followed — Red Hat footprint expanded. ATG — lifecycle ownership from year one. Seven consecutive years of node growth. That's compounding ARR, not a one-time deal. Region Skåne — standardization-led expansion. More nodes, more clusters, new products. These aren't unicorns. This is what the lifecycle model does."</p>
    </aside>
  </section>

  <!-- 8. When to Call -->
  <section>
    <div class="container">
      <h1 style="text-align:center;">
        When to <span class="highlight">Call Stakater</span>
      </h1>
      <br/><br/>
      <div style="display:grid; grid-template-columns:1fr 1fr; gap:50px;">

        <div style="padding:36px; background:#F5F5F5; border-radius:12px;">
          <h3 style="color:#FF5623; margin-bottom:12px; font-size:20px; font-weight:600;">Account with 2+ Clusters</h3>
          <p style="font-size:18px; color:#1A0D32; line-height:1.6;">
            Multi-cluster is the inflection point for ACM and standardization conversations.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div style="padding:36px; background:#F5F5F5; border-radius:12px;">
          <h3 style="color:#FF5623; margin-bottom:12px; font-size:20px; font-weight:600;">Flat Nodes at Renewal</h3>
          <p style="font-size:18px; color:#1A0D32; line-height:1.6;">
            We break the plateau before the renewal conversation gets difficult.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div style="padding:36px; border-left:4px solid #FF5623;">
          <h3 style="margin-bottom:12px; font-size:20px; font-weight:600;">Customer Asking "What's Next?"</h3>
          <p style="font-size:18px; color:#1A0D32; line-height:1.6;">
            Platform maturity assessment. We identify the next product adoption moment.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div style="padding:36px; border-left:4px solid #FF5623;">
          <h3 style="margin-bottom:12px; font-size:20px; font-weight:600;">Post-Implementation Silence</h3>
          <p style="font-size:18px; color:#1A0D32; line-height:1.6;">
            Delivery team disengaged. No one owns the platform. We step in and create momentum.
          </p>
        </div>

      </div>
    </div>

    <aside class="notes">
      <p class="notes-dir">These are practical triggers — invite the AE to think of specific accounts as you go through each.</p>
      <p class="notes-say">"Four signals. Any account with two or more clusters — that's the ACM conversation. Any account with flat nodes coming into renewal — call us before the renewal, not during it. Any customer asking 'what's next?' — we run a platform maturity assessment and identify the pull-through play. And post-implementation silence: if the delivery team is gone and nobody is driving the platform, that's the highest-risk state. We step in, own it, and create momentum."</p>
    </aside>
  </section>

  <!-- 9. CTA -->
  <section class="cta">
    <div class="container" style="text-align:center;">
      <h1>Let's Find the Pull-Through Plays.</h1>
      <br/><br/>
      <h2>
        Share your at-risk renewals.<br/>
        We'll identify where portfolio adoption lives.
      </h2>
      <br/><br/><br/>
      <h1 style="font-weight:800;">
        Bigger Deals. Stickier Platforms. Protected Renewals.
      </h1>
    </div>

    <aside class="notes">
      <p class="notes-dir">Close with a concrete next step. Make it low friction.</p>
      <p class="notes-say">"The ask is simple. Share two or three at-risk renewals from your book — accounts where adoption is flat or you're worried about the renewal conversation. We'll come back to you with a pull-through map: which products make sense, when to introduce them, and what the platform needs to get there. Bigger deals, stickier platforms, renewals you can defend. That's the outcome."</p>
    </aside>
  </section>

</Deck>
